title: For Sale:  SOLD - WTS Dragunov SVD Norinco NDM 86 7.62 NATO
postcontent:
SOLD

Up for sale is currently my last Norinco NDM 86 in 7.62 NATO. Will also fire .308 Winchester. As stated before these rifles are tack drivers, with 1-MOA and sub-MOA possible out of the box. I have sold several of these over my time of collecting, and am willing to provide referrences to ease the minds of buyers.
 The only true copy of the Russian SVD made, one of only 1000 in the country. The rifle has only 20 rounds fired through it for barrel break in. It also has the spring loaded firing pin. The finish overall is near entirely intact with wear only on the moving parts and a few scratches from handling and mounting the scope.
 Comes with accessories, including the manual, 10 round magazine, infra-red detection scope, spare bulb, cleaning rods, oil bottle, and scope box, all new and unused.

title: For Sale/Trade:  NAA .22 MAG w/wallet style holster
postcontent:
I purchased this from a dealer on this site.  It's a beautifully built little revolver.  I've fired 5 rounds (1 full cylinder) through it.  I can tell you that this isn't a long range weapon.  This is an up-close and personal jam it in their eye socket or ear and pull the trigger weapon (or at least for me).  The .22 WMR is a very capable little round and what could be more reliable than a single action stainless steel revolver.  I purchased it as a concealed carry weapon for the summer months.  It's hard to shove my glock in a pair of shorts or under a t-shirt and have it go un-noticed.  Either loose in a pocket or in the nifty little wallet holster it is an easy to conceal little gun.  

Why do I want rid of it?  I want a bow.  I've decided that I want to bow hunt this year and I would like to either get cash to put towards a bow or make a clean trade on a decent used bow.  I dropped right at $300 to buy the little pistol and the slick wallet holster.  The holster is well made, heavy leather, molded to the revolver and has a pouch that holds an additional 5 rounds (1 full cylinder).  It fits in your pocket and conceals the outline of the pistol.  

This is the same revolver you might have seen used to take a monster of a gator on Swamp People a few weeks ago.  It's small but mighty.

For those of you who like to have your belt match your shoes, there are a myriad of accesories for these things, pocket clips, lasers, fancier grips, belt buckles that serve as holsters, etc...

I still have the factory plastic box and paperwork as well.

The STEYR USR AUG 5.56x45mm (.223) caliber in olive stock 
Interchangeable 508mm (20”), with gas regulator and swing/pivot type barrel grip. Cold hammer forged. Chrome lined bore including chamber. Weight empty is 7.9lbs, with over length of 31” and height of 11”. Detachable synthetic (transparent) staggered type 30 round magazine weighing 5 oz. empty.

- 3000 USRs were imported. These were the last all-Austrian to come in and who knows if they will be allowed again

make your rifle incompliant
- Also, most of the Steyr AUG/A3’s don't come with any optics or sights. So if someone brags about picking up a new AUG at $2000 (plus fees) off the internet, add in the cost of an optic. Steyr Optics will set you back $799

I am an amateur gun refinisher that loves to take old, battered, banged up guns and make them shine again.  My experience so far has been with old single barreled shotguns, Marlin mid 60's, an antique musket, and a mosin nagant.  

I have recently run out of projects and am on the search for more.  So if you have an old rifle, shotgun, or milsurp weapon sitting around gathering dust or rusting away then let me know!

Here is what I do:

1.  Research the firearm to make sure refinishing won't ruin any collectors value.
2.  I tear down the entire firearm, clean all internals and lubricate all friction points.
3.  I strip and sand down the old stock to base wood.
4.  Apply a new wood stain of either your or my choosing.
5.  Apply at least 10 layers of tru-oil gunstock finishing oil.
6.  Order and replace any and all parts required to get the gun running again.
7.  Reassemble the gun, test fire, and apply a final oil.

What's the cost to you?  Just parts and supplies...so anywhere from $20 on up depending on parts.  I do not charge labor, as I love doing this as a hobby.

I cannot do checkering, so if your stock has checkering then what I can do is limited.

Thank you for your time!  Examples of my work can be emailed upon request.

title: For Sale:  Pop-up targets
postcontent:
I have started making pop-up targets for my own personal use and will be offering those targets up to others who wish to add a stronger element to their training or just something different for plinking days.

Construction:  Wood and PVC (fully replacable parts)
Target type:  Pop-up
What the Pop-up does:  It's a pin-activated target that can pop-up and stay up, it can pop-up and drop back down, it can start in the  up position and transition down, or it can be set to be up all the time.  This target can be activated from the front, the rear, or the sides so that if you choose to run multiple targets you can run them in series so that one will activate another.

These are adjustable-speed targets.  All you need to do is add or remove sand to the front or the counterweight to adjust the timing.  You can adjust how fast it comes up as well as how fast it will come down.

Each will have been test-fitted and fully tested for functionality before being disassembled for transport.  You can pick it up fully assembled if you like or we can meet at a range that will allow this target and you can try it out when you buy it.  I will include one set of uprights with each target so you can mount your cardboard or paper targets.

Note:  I will not allow measurements to be taken and buyers need to be fully aware that if you want to try one out you must commit to the buy prior to.  Wait time is 1-2 weeks, but if I get one completed quickly I will contact those buyers on a first come, first served basis.

DO NOT shoot at these targets in the down position.  You WILL destroy the target.
